title: Live updates: High school football Week 9
text:
Order a reprint of this story 
Scott County's Noah Hughes, left, slaps hands with Bryan Hudson after Hughes scored a touchdown against Lafayette at Ishmael Stadium in Lexington, Ky., Friday, September 18, 2015. Photo by Matt Goins 
The 2015 high school football season enters Week 9 on Friday night around Kentucky, and Kentucky.com and the Lexington Herald-Leader are where you're going to want to be to follow the action. 
Below are some helpful links to scores, live video broadcasts and additional high school football information. 
You may also scroll down to read live Twitter updates from games around the state from a plethora of media members working games on Friday night.
